Back when I started tattooing, I'd have 2-3 clients a day... so it was, get em in and bang em out. We took appointments and walk-ins, but no consultations... so you never knew what you might get that day. It could be anything from a Kanji to starting a half back ;-) The designs were also simpler to allow for this... it was a good experience and fun to look back on after all these years. Unfortunately Peter lost track of
time (and me) after I left the studio and started Skin&Bone... so it was good to get back at it again. I didn't have to do any drawing this time so we could just jump back into it. I freshened up the outline with some thicker lines and started the dotshading. We're about 6 hours in and making good progress, so should be finished in just two visits and in time for Spring ;-)

#JegErFanThe change in the restrictions regarding metal detecting in Danmark has resulted in many new finds in the last several years. Not only is this a source of history, but it also provides inspiration for traditional woodworkers, embroiderers, silversmiths and even tattooists. However transscribing any designs into another medium requires a bit of knowledge regarding the art. I really enjoy tattooing historical designs, but it often requires thatÂ  I change the design in order to make it suitable as a tattoo. Alot of the details in a three dimensional design can't be seen when drawn on a flat surface due to foreshortening and rounding curves. Similarly many smaller details will not hold in the skin as they will spread and fade over the years. I try to break the design down to basics and use as much negative space as possible to make a design with strong graphics that will survive the test of time.  This fibula/brooch was found in Denmark last week with a human face on a bird's body... many are calling it Odin, while my preference is more toward Loki. I contacted the Detectorist responcible for the find about if he wanted it as a tattoo... however he said that he wasn't really a tattoo person. However I still really want to do this design, so I will be offering a cut rate to the first person to receive this :-) Of course it will be tattooed without machine, using tools which could have been found at the time ;-)
I've also included a few photos of other historical designs I've tattooed using hand tools, to show that just because it is done by hand doesn't mean it has to be rough ;-)
â€¢
â€¢
â€¢

#labyrinth #labyrinthoflight #benjaminnoir #madsvegas #amager #lightdesign #lightinstallation #cphlightfest #lysfestival #copenhagen #kÃ¸benhavn #visitcopenhagen #igerscopenhagen #longexposure #nightphotography #winterwalk #canon6dFiskesuppe. 
Scandinavian fish soup with salmon, codfish, potatoes, carrots, and cream.

Complete experience, including the fish boat in Kastrup harbour.

For the soup base, slow-fry an onion and leek on butter, then add a glass of white wine and let evaporate. Add the potatoes and carrots and fish stock, and let it simmer for some 10 min. Then add the codfish and salmon, cook for a few more minutes, season with cream and pepper, and serve with dild and salmon eggs. 
This soup tastes much better the day after, but  will there be any left?? #amagerlove #seasonalproduce #torsk #kastruphavn #localingredients #fishingharbour #amager #danishmodern #fiskesuppe #freshingredients #pescatarian #scandinaviandesign #salmon #healthyfood #ideasfordinner #nordiccuisine #realfood #fishsoup #kastrupSundown at Kastrup Fortress. With view over Amager Beach.

THE CLASMAN
SCOTCH ALE / WEE HEAVY 
Around the year 200 AD many Highland Scots were seriously fed up. The local whisky industry had almost been wiped out by cheap imported plonk from Roman merchants south of Hadrianâ€™s Wall. Add to that, that for a few decades the weather had been even more miserable than normal due to drifting pollution from the Lowlands.  Some Clansmen, on an assigned royal mission, had navigated south and found nice beaches on Mallorca, but they also found the Balearic Islands to be overcrowded by way too many Spanish. So King Dargart ordered his best seamen further south in the Atlantic with strict orders not to return before they had found a pleasant stretch of land with nice beaches, few people and a proper base for whisky production.  Dargart had to wait quite some time, but finally one day a post card arrived, stamped in a place called Jubim, Brazil. The post card â€“ actually a polaroid photo â€“ showed the Kingâ€™s men all jolly while still deeply focused on their game of beach volleyball, red-bellied in their yellow Speedos. â€œPlenty of land and water, no people, nice weather. Please bring barley seed and sun lotionâ€ was all the card read. This is the historical background for the little known Scottish colony â€œCaledonian Wonderlandâ€ in what is today called Brazil. A colony that existed and prospered peacefully for several hundred years until one day a lookout saw a flotilla of square sail longships approaching on the horizonâ€¦.

THE VIKING
Stout
The Vikings are known from Russia to North America as eminent sailors and navigators. But one Viking expedition led by the brave Deirik the Disoriented has always puzzled historians, because it simply vanished completely. Today we know better.  Wanting to take his whole crew to see Cats the Musical on Broadway, Deirik simply took a wrong turn in the middle of the Atlantic. His navigational sunstone claimed they were going west, but in reality their course was much more southerly. When the exhausted crewmen finally caught sight of land, a feeling of joy and relief went through everybody, as the land seemed both warm, fertile and welcoming.  So the frustration was immense when they were welcomed on shore, not by local beauties covering them in flowers, but by a flock of portly and pink Scotsmen wearing nothing but overly tight trunks.  The Vikings, tired from the long cruise, mercifully refrained from killing the unkilted Clansmen, and the two nations actually lived in peace for a few weeks.  One night however, a heated discussion as to whether Brewdog or Mikkeller was the best beer in the world led to hostilities breaking out. The battle went on for days in what has been called The Great Nordic War in the Tropics, until only a few Vikings were left standing as the lone survivors. Their destiny however is shrouded in a mist of mystery. But the ticket girl at Cats on Broadway insists that she never sold one single ticket to a Viking for the whole nine years the show ran.
5.7%
Br : Amager @amagerbryghus

Siden 1980 har Fabricius drevet forlaget Space Poetry, og har udgivet en rÃ¦kke bÃ¸ger, kunstkataloger, digtsamlinger og mere avantgarde bogobjekter. Kunstneren udgiver ogsÃ¥ kunsttidsskriftet, Pist Protta - som siden 1981 har formidlet alternativ kunsthistorie. Husk jeg meget gerne sender varer - det koster 45 kr. og er fragtfrit ved kÃ¸b over 500 kr. ğŸ“®ğŸ‘ŒğŸ¼âœ”ï¸Viewpoint Coco, Imperial Stout 11% Amager Bryghus Kastrup Denmark in collaboration with Cervejaria DÃ¡diva Varzea Paulista, Sao Paulo Brazil.

A Danish / Brazilian collaboration this time from Amager and DÃ¡diva.
There are 2 versions of this imperial stout, the original version is Goiabada stout with guava and this 2nd version with coconut, which is also a double maisch version of it, as Amager says.. 'to really fuck up shit'
I have both versions of the beer and started with the coconut version last night while watching a VAR killing a football game in Amsterdam (UEFA mafia)
But let's stick to the beer.
This is double maisch Viewpoint coconut version is a really thick and creamy stout when it comes to mouthfeel.
There is a lot of chocolate in flavor and next to that a lot of coffee, some sweetness on this side (Is that the guave?) sweet liquorice, In the finish a shot of bitterness which tasted like a coffee bitter. I didn't taste anything of the coconut though!
If it is there is really hiding behind those thick layers of chocolate and coffee flavors, and has really a hard time reaching out and climbing over those other flavors.
What is left is a thick and intense stout with loads of coffee and chocolate, is that good, i say yes, but if your out for a coconut hunt.... you will not find it there.
4*
Cheers

Entrate mai nelle biblioteche? Vi regna una pace indescrivibile. A Copenaghen sono tante, da quella storica con gli interni in legno a quella moderna con le facciate in vetro che danno sul canale. E poi ce ne sono tante altre sparse per la cittÃ , che se uno non si ferma un attimo, nemmeno le riconosce. Eppure sono dei luoghi fantastici dove noi amiamo entrare anche solo per un po'. Nelle biblioteche possiamo studiare, leggere, consultare i libri a disposizione, ma anche fermarci a riflettere approfittando del silenzio che vi regna. Qui le biblioteche sono anche luoghi ideali dove organizzare un colloquio o un tandem linguistico, come ho fatto io oggi insieme ad un collega!
Buon pomeriggio!

EnergimÃ¦rke DWhen I moved into this building on #Amager in 2002 with a #Zimbabwean/#SouthAfrican, his cousin visited us on a day where someone had also stuck the #Danish flag on the bannister. 'Do you have a hardcore nationalist living in the building?', the cousin asked.

I explained how #Danes - innocently - use the flag to celebrate birthdays, not nationalism. However, I'm still contemplating the cousin's observation, and flags still make me reconsider how an innocent birthday celebration may look like a demarcation of #Danishness to the cousin who grew up in #apartheid #SouthAfrica. It made me think of how we appear to the stranger.

We need more people who pull on other #cultural heritages to observe us and ask us questions. It may make us wiser.Hos Senses Amagerbro kan du dyrke yoga, hot yoga, reformertrÃ¦ning og barretrÃ¦ning. A dear friend brought these pale yellow, fragrant tulips. Pure joy for a week. Now theyâ€™re rearranged from vases to a ceramic dish #townhouse #sundby #amager #kÃ¸benhavn #cph #tulipsareamazingandgraceful #springiscoming #tulipsThe Copenhagen Metro ğŸš‡ part 2 - Escalators are inset from the outer walls and have glass sides to allow as much light as possible to get down to the platform from above. A common arrangement in other metro systems is to have pairs of escalators side by side with one going up and one down and with the same arrangement repeated at either end of a long platform. In the Copenhagen system, within the tight space of the box, there are two escalators going down at one end and two moving up at the other. To go down you start at the outside edge of the space and go down to a landing where you move towards the centre and double back with two escalators together side by side going down to the centre of the platform â€¦ if it was laid out the other way, with the two upper escalators together, the lower flights would be on the outside against the track. 
#metro #station #metrostation #copenhagen #delditkbh #architecture #arkitektur #rulletrappe #sharingcph #deldinby #kÃ¸benhavn #delditkbh #commute #escalator #amager #visitamager #khrarkitekter #visitcopenhagen #transport #architecture #denmark #ğŸš‡#sharingcph #kigopkbh #khrarchitects #voreskbh #kÃ¸benhavnThe Copenhagen Metro ğŸš‡ part 1 - There are twenty-two stations on the network, of which nine are underground and six are deep-level. They were all designed by KHR Arkitekter, who created open stations with daylight. The six deep-level stations are built as rectangular, open boxes 60Â m (200Â ft) long, 20Â m (66Â ft) wide and 20Â m (66Â ft) deep. The platforms are located 18Â m (59Â ft) below the surface. Access to the surface is reached via escalators and elevators. There are glass pyramids on the roof of the stations permitting daylight to enter. Inside the pyramids, there are prismsreflecting and splitting the light, sometimes resulting in rainbows on the walls. The light in the stations is automatically regulated to make best use of the daylight and maintain a constant level of illumination of the stations at all times.

#mango #mangoicecream #mangois #kaffe #istid #kaffee #paradiseis #paradisicecream #icecream #vegan #veganoptions #vegans #onlyicecream #icecreamporn #virginmojito #fieldsshoppingcenter #amager #copenhagen #Ã¸ko #Ã¸kologisk #Ã¸kologi #organic #organicicecream #handmade #handmadeicecream #Ã¸kologiskis #Ã¸restad #icecreamlover #visitamager #icecreamtimeIf you happen to be lucky enough to find yourself in Copenhagen this month, do pop along to the Amager Musiktorvet. 
As part of the 2019 @cphlightfest, our talented friends at @chaos.engine have created â€œSynthetic Iciclesâ€ - an audiovisual installation inspired by the increasingly endangered Pacific walrus. Each of the nine incandescent "tusks" contains 500 RGB LEDs spread over five 2.5m-long strips. Controlled using an #ENTTEC Storm 24, the whole pulsating, psychedelic light show is accompanied by the ethereal sound of walrus calls. 
The installation runs until February 24th, daily from from 5pm to midnight. 
Photos by Malene Nelting Jepsen ğŸ“· 
#Storm24 #lightart #LightingDesigner #LightingDesign #LightArt #amagerkulturpunkt #amagerbio #musiktorvet #musicplazacopenhagen #amager #tusk #icicles #installationart #cphlightfest #cphlightfestival #cphlightfestival2019 #cphlightfest2019 #visitcopenhagenBaby Wombat From Hell, Porter 6% Amager Bryghus Kastrup Denmark.

It's a long time ago I had a beer from Amager that isn't a collab.
I was looking on the bottle but could not find any collaborating breweries on the label this time, this doesn't happen to often... lonely times at the Kastrup breweries.
Maybe their baby wombat had scared the other's away, who knows.
Of course their is a long text on the bottle without saying about the beer itself, also that is Amager ;)
The label is as beautiful as always, with the artwork from Simon Hartvig Daugaard.
Baby Wombat from Hell is a classic styled porter.
Silky smooth mouthfeel, chocolate in the front seat, next in line coffee, a tiny little roast on the side and little nutty flavor in the finish.
It's tasty, solid and it showcases a lot of chocolate without being totally outspoken, typical classic porter i would say.
Can't go wrong with this beer.
3.75*
Cheers

And so it begins @icescreenprinting working his magic ğŸ¤˜ğŸ»2 color print in medieval bronze and trve black death. Coming soon ğŸ¤˜ğŸ»Lidt bekymret for om knÃ¦gten fÃ¥r lÃ¦rt at stave. Men godt der er stavekontrol i word. #intranet #skole #amager #staveplade #dansklÃ¦rer #dansk #stavning #undervisning #lektierThis is the last of four from the Wicked Tales Of Scotland series from Amager Bryghus. .
.
Black Donald is a Laphriog whisky barrel aged heavily peated Imperial Stout.
.
.
Heavily peated ? So I expected a more extreme stout with this one. From the aroma of peat, whisky and smoke it lent itself towards that thinking...and in the drinking as the bold whisky and smokiness was very much at the forefront on first sip. Still quite sweet with roasted malt, chocolate, caramel and some dark dried fruit in the back. Finishes mildly bitter with whisky and smoked peat. Earthy smoke in the aftertaste. Full bodied.
.
.
A very nice sipper to spend an hour with. Ive really enjoyed this series with possibly yesterdays The Boobrie being my favourite though all have been 'up there'. All are well worth a visit if you haven't tried them.
.
.
I'll leave this series with my own very short Tale from Scotland : The Doo : A doo is Dundonian dialect for pidgeon. One night when very young I got to stay up late and got to see the Hitchcock film 'The Birds'. This film absolutely traumatised me. Honestly, I was shit scared of doo's for bloody ages. What didn't help was we lived in a high rise at the time and I'm  sure the same friggin beady eyed wee bastard bird perched on our balcony day after day looking in the window, it freaked me out ! A phobia was born...To this day I still hate the flying fucken vermin...This is more believable than when I seen the White Lady of Balgay Bridge (Google it, 'tis real) however I had eaten some magic mushrooms at the time so I can't confirm it happened. Don't do drugs kids.ğŸ•º Cheers ! ğŸ»

Brewery : @amagerbryghus
.
Beer : Black Donald . 11 % abv.
.
Rating :  A stingy 4/5 ğŸºğŸºğŸºğŸº
.
Shop : @boxbeerscom
.

.
.
.
.

I dag blev musen hjemme bare lige som en ekstra dag til at blive helt rask, vi valgte at tage barnevognen gÃ¥ ned til bussen og tage en lille tur i fields og kÃ¸be badesandaler til mig, da jeg skal have fjernet noget af mine tÃ¥negle i morgen og ikke regner med at kunne have almindelige sko pÃ¥ ğŸ˜± det var suuuper hyggeligt.

Men ellers gÃ¥r det meget godt ğŸ˜… #photooftheday #sygtbarn #barsel #minebÃ¸rn #didriksons1913 #wonderfullchildren #amager #sÃ¥danerlivet #bloggerlife #mommyblogReview 1759 - Black Donald - Amager Bryghus - Imperial Stout - ABV 11.0% - Bottle from @boxbeerscom - Well, another special series of brews has been released by @amagerbryghus - "The Wicked Tales of Scotland" - four different beers barrel aged on different Scottish whisky barrels. The Black Donald has been aged on Laphroaig barrels for 8 months, and even if I'm not a super-fan of smokey beers, I do love Laphroaig. For everyones safety I try to stay away from hard liquor, but once in a while I allow myself to sip on the ol' Scottish lemonade called whisky. And there's no doubt, not even for a second, that it's BA:d on Laphroaig barrels. The aroma is unistakably Laphroaig-ish. Aroma is dark and roasted with an earthy touch and notoriusly peaty. Taste is sweet with copius amounts of whisky, a little too much actually, with a deep, low roasted finish. Very light chocolate and then the big peated ending. I do think that it has too much of Laphroaig in here, but if you let it rest for a while in the glass, it grows on you. Or maybe it's just the brain that adjusts (if you have one?). In the end I think that it is quite enjoyable, but the whisky is overpowering. An evening sipper. 3.5/5.0 #wickedtalesofscotland #amager #amagerbryghus #blackdonald #imperialstout #barrelagedbeer #boxbeerscom #thebeernation #hopmaestro #danishcraftbeer #boxbeersLys under Langebro 
#islandsbrygge #bryggen #amager #copenhagen #kÃ¸benhavn #cosycopenhagen #lysfestThis is the third of four from the Wicked Tales Of Scotland series from Amager Bryghus. .
.
The Boobrie is a Glen Garioch whisky barrel aged double mashed Imperial Stout.
.
.
I've seen on my feed some hype on this one as Amager through the years have made some absolute cracking top class stouts, so to put it right in their top 5 from this brewery had my expectations raised..
.
.
A good whiff of oak and whisky from the pour. Pretty sweet going down with lots of roast, chocolate, toffee, treacle fudge, whisky, oak and hints of vanilla. Finishes with a good whack of bitterness leaving oak, whisky and treacle in the sticky lips aftertaste. .
.
With a stronger abv than the first two from this series I was a bit worried the alcohol might be hot, not so, it's just warming. Great stuff and yeah it's right up in a top 5 from them. Tremendous sipper.
.
.
They should have made a 5th WTOS brew entitled ' Fit like min ?,This is REAL stout ya pastry stout limp wristed cheating bastards, GIRFUY'.....
.

.
Beer : The Boobrie. 12 % abv.
.

I like cats but I hate black ones....evil wee shites imo, I hope I like the beer better....
.
.
The Black Cat is a Bowmore whisky barrel aged peated Baltic Porter. The whisky/peat is much more noticeable in the aroma than yesterdays. Pitch black pour with a quick dissipating head leaving an oily resin on top.
.
.
Any fear I had about not liking this was put to bed on first sip and left a wee smile on my face with its roasted malt, coffee, dark chocolate and cinder toffee giving way to some warm oaky whisky goodness and smoked peat in the finish. Whisky lingers in the aftertaste. Really soft mouthfeel. Full bodied and quite sweet.
.
.
Damn damn damn this was nice, so much so that I forgot about the warming alcohol going down. .
.
No buts with this one either so I leave with a Fact or Fiction tale from Scotland......The Stars And Stripes : when I was four I had my first encounter with the American flag, except it was in the form of a large v for victory hand sign sticker on my bedroom door.  Why you may ask ? Well one day the lock got stuck and my dad kicked a hole right through the door with steel toe cappers on...it was a surreal thing to see a man with his leg stuck in a door at that age ğŸ˜‚ To cover the hole he stuck the large stars and stripes sticker on....I never realized what they were was until I went to school. Fact ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚
.
.

.

.

LÃ¦kker 18 Ã¥rsğŸ¤ª

#myselfiestation #nexusevent #18Ã¥rs #amager #skÃ¸nnemenneskerWith my head nearly bursting with cold/flu this is a perfect time to take a break from the hoppier side of life and have some warming BA beers and imperials. Beer of the day is the first of 4 from the Wicked Tales Of Scotland barrel aged series from Amager Bryghus.
.
.
Red Cap is a Auchentoshan whisky barrel aged Wee Heavy. Pours very dark brown. Malt, caramel and biscuits dominate my initial impression then it settles with roast, berries, toast, oak, peat and some chocolate. Finishes fruity, rich and malty with a non overpowering taste of oak soaked whisky. Full bodied
.
.
Talk about perfect timing for a beer as this hit the snot laden spot with its gentle warming going down. This went down well.... Normally I finish with a 'but' , there is none here although I have always wondered why people from the west coast of Scotland finish sentences with it.  Example : 'am away up the road but'. ..but fucken what ? ğŸ¤”
.
.
Rating : A generous 4/5 ğŸºğŸºğŸºğŸº
.
Brewery : @amagerbryghus
.
Beer : Red Cap Wee Heavy BA. 9.5% abv
.
One more please /One off : One off.
.
Shop : @boxbeerscom .
.
.
.
.
.

#Amager Arctic Sun Stone #PaleAle, Ratebeer review : It pours hazy deep orange color with short lasting off-white head. Inviting aroma, it smells strongly orange, pine and slightly floral. Taste is moderately high bitter and low to moderate sweet. High grapefruity fruitiness comes first, but caramelly and honey like maltiness is in background. Dry and spicy finish. Very soft and tasty bitterness stays in aftertaste. Medium bodied and carbonation is low to moderate. It's a highly drinkable and highly refreshing hoppy Pale Ale.#denmark #danmark #copenhagen #kÃ¸benhavn #voreskbh #amager #amagerbladet #sundby #amagerbrogade #nyamagerbrogade #gade #street #streetsnap #steetphoto #gadefotografi #gadefoto #streetculture #streetphotography #streetwear #streetlife #street_vision #gadeliv #streetlife #balloner #palloncini #balloons

Copenhagen Light Festival 2019. 
#copenhagenlightfestival2019 #taraxa #cphlightfestival #gungordillo #sustainableunderwaterlight #goboat #islandsbrygge #amager #copenhagenlightfestival #wonderfulcopenhagen #kÃ¸benhavnk #cphpicks #kÃ¸benhavnerbilleder #mitkÃ¸benhavn #minby #deldinby #delditkÃ¸benhavn #luluskÃ¸benhavn #marilouscopenhagen #jegelskerminby #gadebilleder #streetphotography #bestcopenhagen #cozycopenhagen #visitcopenhagen #go2copenhagen @cphlightfestBillie's Bier Kafetaria heeft met Billie The Butcher een lekkere eigen DDH (Double Dry Hopped) IPA in huis. Ze zijn hem gaan brouwen bij Amager Bryghus in Kopenhagen, maar naar een eigen recept.  Fruitige aroma's en een lekkere bitter, zoals een IPA moet zijn. Een bezoek hier stond al veel te lang op mijn to-do lijst en nu heb ik er spijt van dat ik er niet veel eerder ben langsgeweest!

With Billie The Butcher, Billie's Bier Kafetaria has its own tasty DDH (Double Dry Hopped) IPA. They went to brew it at Amager Bryghus in Copenhagen, but the recipe is completely theirs. A lot of fruit in the aroma and a nice bitter, like an IPA should be. A visit here was long overdue and now I regret it took so long!

#grÃ¸nfrisÃ¸r #grÃ¸nsalon #renskÃ¸nhed #frisÃ¸rkÃ¸benhavn #kÃ¸benhavnk #kongensnytorv #amager #christianshavn #frederiksberg #nÃ¸rrebro #nÃ¸rreport #vesterbro #Ã¸sterbro #sydhavnen #pandehÃ¥r #sÃ¸ndag @eshakhamoReview 1749 - Buffalo Burlesque - Amager Bryghus - Imperial Stout - ABV 11.0% - Bottle from @boxbeerscom - Stout Sunday with @amagerbryghus , with an excellent soundtrack in the form of Funeral Mist "Hekatomb". The best album in 2018 according to my standards. This badboy (or badgirl rather) was barrel aged for 8 months on Bordeaux red wine barrels. That made me a bit suspicious, 'cause red wine is not my go-to drink. I don't drink wine at all actually. But, I like to challenge myself, so here we go. Aroma is rich. Roasted malts with coffee notes and licorice. A light herbal scent as well. Taste is straight up Amager stout with rich roasted malts, cocoa, coffee and an almost spicey taste. The red wine barrels here, sends character and that vineous bite in the aftertaste sure gives a different take. I don't really dig that though, sorry for that, but all in all it's another great stout from the Danes. 3.75/5.0 #amager #amagerbryghus #buffaloburlesque #imperialstout #barrelagedbeer #funeralmist #hekatomb #danishcraftbeer #boxbeerscom #drinkitlikeyoumeanit #hopmaestro #boxbeersDaddys LiL Helper @ www.pioma.dk & #teamwhitebelt - #basicjiujitsu #jiujitsu #jiujitsulifestyle #pioma #progressiveinstituteofmartialarts #tactical #strategy #martialarts #selfdefense #combatives #kampkunst #kampsport #selvforsvar #copenhagen #kÃ¸benhavn #amager #sundby #kunst #art #urban #street #daddysgirl #fatherandaughter #family #legacyThe kids wanted visit Daddy @ www.pioma.dk #pioma #progressiveinstituteofmartialarts #fatheranddaughter #fatherandson #daddysgirl #family #legacy @ www.pioma.dk & #teamwhitebelt - #basicjiujitsu #jiujitsu #jiujitsulifestyle #pioma #progressiveinstituteofmartialarts #tactical #strategy #martialarts #selfdefense #combatives #kampkunst #kampsport #selvforsvar #copenhagen #kÃ¸benhavn #amager #sundby #kunst #art #urban #streetWarm up whit the mayor here in Sittingburne. Naturpark Amager covers an extensive and varied area of close to 35 km2. Creating coherence and visual links throughout the park is both the challenge and the potential.
